# SHA-256 checksums for real-world PE binaries fetched by
# scripts/fetch-real-pe-binaries.sh.
#
# Format: <sha256>  <filename>
#
# These are the *upstream-published* sums for pinned releases. If an
# upstream vendor rotates a release in place (frippery does occasionally,
# curl.se does not), update the pin URL + sum together and note the
# rotation in the matching session log.
#
# Format is compatible with `sha256sum -c SHA256SUMS` (GNU coreutils).
# Files that are present but not listed here are IGNORED by -c (and are
# re-verified in the fetch script against the pinned sum inline).

# --- busybox-w32 (FRP-5034-g15892753a) -- single-file Unix-tools
# binary, 64-bit PE. Imports: kernel32, msvcrt. ~500 KB.
# Source: https://frippery.org/files/busybox/busybox-w64-FRP-5034-g15892753a.exe
# Pinned: 2024-02-18 release.
4d4d6c7fdd5e8f4b9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e9e  busybox64.exe

